1
00:00:00,086 --> 00:00:03,430
My old partner he had hepatitis.

2
00:00:04,468 --> 00:00:05,573
- What?
- What?

3
00:00:06,709 --> 00:00:08,063
What I said yesterday was that

4
00:00:08,063 --> 00:00:11,200
If it's a visit to see each other,
I don't object to that.

5
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:13,800
But not to have him move in
and become a burden like this.

6
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:18,680
So, all of us, the Fab Family,

7
00:00:19,520 --> 00:00:21,320
we take turns looking after her?

8
00:00:21,895 --> 00:00:24,575
Let her go peacefully,
just the way she wants.

9
00:00:25,040 --> 00:00:28,000
May Mae Champi
receive Monk Thai's merit,

10
00:00:28,360 --> 00:00:30,640
and take an elevator
to the highest levels of heaven.

11
00:00:31,056 --> 00:00:32,760
- Amen to that.
- Amen to that.

12
00:01:04,685 --> 00:01:05,920
Are you worried, Jee?

13
00:01:09,518 --> 00:01:10,518
Yeah.

14
00:01:14,370 --> 00:01:16,360
Don't overthink it.

15
00:01:16,360 --> 00:01:19,280
It might turn out to be nothing.

16
00:01:33,065 --> 00:01:36,520
I'm 55 now.
I have to think about these things.

17
00:01:38,188 --> 00:01:40,480
Birth, aging, sickness, and death,
it's the truth of life.

18
00:01:43,860 --> 00:01:45,906
What happened to Mae Champi...

19
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:49,880
one day, it'll happen to us too.

20
00:01:57,147 --> 00:01:59,480
Fine, I'm wide awake now.

21
00:02:00,600 --> 00:02:01,887
Are you happy now?

22
00:02:16,705 --> 00:02:18,805
"Tonight, we both can't sleep."

23
00:03:02,720 --> 00:03:04,133
It's heartbreaking, isn't it?

24
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:08,280
At least we knew in advance.
We had time to prepare.

25
00:03:09,260 --> 00:03:11,400
But for a very short time.

26
00:03:11,879 --> 00:03:14,720
As soon as we found out,
she was already in the final stage.

27
00:03:17,320 --> 00:03:20,147
If only Mae Champi
had a check-up every year,

28
00:03:20,147 --> 00:03:21,313
it probably wouldn't...

29
00:03:21,313 --> 00:03:24,500
For someone who
doesn't have much to get by,

30
00:03:24,500 --> 00:03:26,386
where would they get
the money for a check-up?

31
00:03:27,985 --> 00:03:29,560
Mmm.

32
00:03:30,040 --> 00:03:32,529
Do you guys ever get check-ups?

33
00:03:32,975 --> 00:03:35,080
I go every year;
Nidnoi drags me along.

34
00:03:36,440 --> 00:03:37,673
You really should.

35
00:03:44,883 --> 00:03:46,960
- Oh.
- This way, Luang Por.

36
00:03:53,590 --> 00:03:56,770
We shall dedicate the merit,
and receive the blessing together.

37
00:04:10,420 --> 00:04:13,480
Come back for
your results in three days.

38
00:04:14,097 --> 00:04:15,320
Yes, sir.

39
00:04:16,801 --> 00:04:17,801
As for you, Jira.

40
00:04:18,440 --> 00:04:20,200
The lump on your neck...

41
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:22,040
But it's only a small lump.

42
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:24,440
Is it just muscle inflammation?

43
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:27,400
I think you should have a biopsy.

44
00:04:28,080 --> 00:04:29,200
A biopsy?

45
00:04:30,560 --> 00:04:32,360
It might just be a benign tumor.

46
00:04:33,094 --> 00:04:34,560
Or...

47
00:04:38,305 --> 00:04:39,625
Cancer?

48
00:04:41,080 --> 00:04:44,600
Worst-case scenario,
it could be lymphoma.

49
00:04:45,717 --> 00:04:47,960
But I need to examine it
before I can say for sure.

50
00:04:49,406 --> 00:04:52,058
If we catch it early,
there's a chance it can be cured.

51
00:04:52,058 --> 00:04:53,480
There's no need to worry.

52
00:04:55,520 --> 00:04:57,840
This biopsy is a minor procedure.

53
00:04:58,400 --> 00:04:59,813
There's nothing to be afraid of.

54
00:04:59,813 --> 00:05:01,880
Just fast from
food and water beforehand.

55
00:05:02,360 --> 00:05:05,040
We'll operate in the morning,
and you'll be home by noon.

56
00:05:05,925 --> 00:05:07,751
Then, we'll wait
two weeks for the results.

57
00:05:09,377 --> 00:05:10,377
Uh...

58
00:05:12,195 --> 00:05:15,600
In three days,
Dr. Kosol is available.

59
00:05:16,226 --> 00:05:17,226
What do you think?

60
00:05:17,653 --> 00:05:19,360
Please book the appointment.

61
00:05:19,676 --> 00:05:21,520
- You want to book it then?
- Yes.

62
00:05:21,520 --> 00:05:22,520
Understood.

63
00:05:53,587 --> 00:05:54,587
Jee.

64
00:05:56,337 --> 00:05:58,920
Did you get any sleep at all?

65
00:06:01,977 --> 00:06:03,120
Endless sleep.

66
00:06:04,117 --> 00:06:05,360
Never to return.

67
00:06:06,211 --> 00:06:07,438
The inescapable truth.

68
00:06:07,438 --> 00:06:10,231
What are you talking about?

69
00:06:10,231 --> 00:06:11,504
Huh?

70
00:06:11,504 --> 00:06:13,251
What do you mean "Endless sleep"?

71
00:06:15,176 --> 00:06:16,230
Come on.

72
00:06:17,292 --> 00:06:18,760
I've been thinking about it.

73
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:21,200
I've finally decided...

74
00:06:22,560 --> 00:06:25,200
how I am going to
divide up my assets.

75
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:27,920
I feel relieved now.

76
00:06:28,927 --> 00:06:30,040
Jee.

77
00:06:31,340 --> 00:06:33,493
Why are you thinking so far ahead?

78
00:06:33,493 --> 00:06:35,560
Well, if it ever comes to that...

79
00:06:36,231 --> 00:06:38,164
to the point where you
have to prolong my life...

80
00:06:40,744 --> 00:06:42,284
you have to let me go, okay?

81
00:06:45,015 --> 00:06:46,355
I don't want to suffer.

82
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:50,560
And I don't want to be
an emotional burden to others.

83
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:53,600
Are you crazy?

84
00:06:54,365 --> 00:06:55,760
What burden?

85
00:06:56,960 --> 00:06:59,160
How could I just let you die?

86
00:07:00,444 --> 00:07:02,280
I don't mean we won't try.

87
00:07:03,080 --> 00:07:06,800
Just, if it reaches
that point of life support...

88
00:07:08,509 --> 00:07:09,649
I'm begging you.

89
00:07:11,381 --> 00:07:12,680
You have to let me go.

90
00:07:13,513 --> 00:07:14,560
Mmm...

91
00:07:16,880 --> 00:07:17,880
No.

92
00:07:19,160 --> 00:07:20,693
I'm naming you

93
00:07:20,693 --> 00:07:24,313
as my designated person
in my Living Will

94
00:07:24,313 --> 00:07:28,360
to decline medical intervention
for prolonging life.

95
00:07:31,524 --> 00:07:33,131
As the "designated person"?

96
00:07:33,131 --> 00:07:38,560
It's the person I trust
to truly carry out my wishes.

97
00:07:39,640 --> 00:07:44,520
For when I'm no longer in a state
to decide for myself.

98
00:07:45,280 --> 00:07:49,820
Like, when I'm on life support,

99
00:07:49,820 --> 00:07:52,600
being on a ventilator
or a feeding tube,

100
00:07:53,358 --> 00:07:55,440
or if I'm permanently unconscious.

101
00:07:56,364 --> 00:08:01,382
Which means, you would be
the one deciding for me.

102
00:08:05,784 --> 00:08:07,010
I don't want to.

103
00:08:08,080 --> 00:08:09,232
No?

104
00:08:09,232 --> 00:08:11,693
Who else am I going to ask?

105
00:08:12,680 --> 00:08:13,860
My parents?

106
00:08:14,233 --> 00:08:15,266
No.

107
00:08:16,818 --> 00:08:18,120
No way.

108
00:08:19,044 --> 00:08:20,164
I'm begging you.

109
00:08:25,002 --> 00:08:27,600
Don't make my parents
face something like that.

110
00:08:34,456 --> 00:08:35,456
Come on.

111
00:08:38,714 --> 00:08:40,760
The reason I want you
to do this is...

112
00:08:42,427 --> 00:08:43,747
because I trust you.

113
00:08:45,771 --> 00:08:47,600
And I know that you love me.

114
00:08:50,033 --> 00:08:51,320
You know me...

115
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:55,440
well enough to make
the right decisions for me.

116
00:09:05,019 --> 00:09:06,019
Fine.

117
00:09:08,214 --> 00:09:10,720
I'll be your designated person.

118
00:09:12,920 --> 00:09:13,920
Thank you.

119
00:09:16,375 --> 00:09:18,160
But can we
stop talking about this now?

120
00:09:19,661 --> 00:09:21,054
It's making me uneasy.

121
00:09:25,009 --> 00:09:26,009
Mmm.

122
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:28,880
There, there...

123
00:09:34,320 --> 00:09:35,466
Until the day we die...

124
00:09:37,021 --> 00:09:38,919
Let's stay together, okay?

125
00:09:53,851 --> 00:09:55,880
Very good. Smells great.

126
00:10:03,920 --> 00:10:04,920
Fever.

127
00:10:05,806 --> 00:10:06,806
Chronic cough.

128
00:10:13,430 --> 00:10:14,436
Jee.

129
00:10:15,317 --> 00:10:16,450
Is something wrong?

130
00:10:16,450 --> 00:10:17,680
Do you have a chronic cough?

131
00:10:18,730 --> 00:10:20,120
Do you have a fever?

132
00:10:28,852 --> 00:10:31,304
Congratulations! Congratulations!

133
00:10:31,304 --> 00:10:32,417
Congrats.

134
00:10:32,417 --> 00:10:34,174
We've checked off one out of six;

135
00:10:34,174 --> 00:10:35,417
only five more to go.

136
00:10:35,417 --> 00:10:37,960
Let's see if Mr. Jira, that's me,

137
00:10:37,960 --> 00:10:42,793
will be the lucky winner
of the cancer lottery.

138
00:10:42,793 --> 00:10:45,893
Come join the excitement
with our viewers at home...

139
00:10:45,893 --> 00:10:48,680
Jee, what kind of madness is this?

140
00:10:48,680 --> 00:10:51,287
Are you so scared
that you've gone mad?

141
00:10:51,287 --> 00:10:52,689
Without further ado,

142
00:10:52,689 --> 00:10:54,920
let's move on to the second card.

143
00:10:54,920 --> 00:10:55,986
Let's go!

144
00:10:58,640 --> 00:11:00,747
Which card?

145
00:11:00,747 --> 00:11:02,580
Oh, I'll open it myself.

146
00:11:02,580 --> 00:11:04,587
I'm the one sick, after all.

147
00:11:04,587 --> 00:11:05,693
Let's go with this one.

148
00:11:06,784 --> 00:11:08,044
Enlarged tonsils.

149
00:11:10,375 --> 00:11:12,235
- Are they enlarged?
- Let's check.

150
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:16,567
Whoa, they're big, really big.

151
00:11:16,567 --> 00:11:19,840
I've never seen anyone
with tonsils this enlarged before.

152
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:23,380
We're getting
very close to the truth.

153
00:11:23,380 --> 00:11:25,500
Wow, I'm getting the chills,

154
00:11:25,500 --> 00:11:27,700
wondering if I'm actually
going to have cancer.

155
00:11:27,700 --> 00:11:30,000
I'm sure everyone at home
must be dying to know by now.

156
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,840
Let's go to the next card!

157
00:11:37,840 --> 00:11:38,993
Loss of appetite.

158
00:11:42,160 --> 00:11:43,160
Itching.

159
00:11:48,876 --> 00:11:50,040
Night sweats.

160
00:11:52,069 --> 00:11:55,000
And the final card.

161
00:11:55,760 --> 00:11:57,800
Can we not open the last one?

162
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:01,040
I'll be rooting for you

163
00:12:01,720 --> 00:12:03,007
to see what's coming.

164
00:12:03,007 --> 00:12:04,560
I believe everyone
wants to know now.

165
00:12:05,520 --> 00:12:07,380
Let's countdown.

166
00:12:07,380 --> 00:12:10,320
Five, four, three, two, one,
here it is.

167
00:12:11,456 --> 00:12:12,762
A lump in the throat.

168
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:24,945
Six out of six.
All of the above

169
00:12:24,945 --> 00:12:27,212
Congratulations, Mr. Ohn.

170
00:12:27,212 --> 00:12:31,360
Your partner is now part of
the statistics of Thai people

171
00:12:31,360 --> 00:12:33,220
who die from cancer,

172
00:12:33,220 --> 00:12:35,600
which is 227 people a day.

173
00:12:37,090 --> 00:12:38,323
Applaud!

174
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:41,640
What are you clapping for?

175
00:12:41,640 --> 00:12:43,840
It's not something
to be happy about.

176
00:12:51,034 --> 00:12:54,560
Ugh, you shouldn't be celebrating.

177
00:12:55,017 --> 00:12:56,234
It's not funny, damn it.

178
00:12:59,258 --> 00:13:01,418
Don't do this, Jee.

179
00:13:01,418 --> 00:13:03,465
Don't accept the cancer crown.

180
00:13:03,465 --> 00:13:07,145
No...

181
00:13:07,145 --> 00:13:08,259
Ohn.

182
00:13:08,709 --> 00:13:10,149
- Ohn.
- Hmm?

183
00:13:11,337 --> 00:13:14,200
What's wrong? Don't want to eat?

184
00:13:15,180 --> 00:13:18,040
No, it's nothing.

185
00:13:18,689 --> 00:13:20,440
Eat, then.

186
00:13:32,202 --> 00:13:33,202
Uh...

187
00:13:34,120 --> 00:13:36,040
Your health seems
to have no issues.

188
00:13:36,880 --> 00:13:39,480
But your total cholesterol
is at 210.

189
00:13:40,082 --> 00:13:42,080
The LDL value is 150.

190
00:13:42,800 --> 00:13:45,360
Triglycerides are 160,
that's right on the edge.

191
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:47,520
Almost every value is a bit high.

192
00:13:48,203 --> 00:13:49,626
But it's not
affecting anything yet.

193
00:13:49,626 --> 00:13:51,086
Try adjusting your diet,

194
00:13:51,458 --> 00:13:53,120
and your eating habits first.

195
00:13:53,640 --> 00:13:56,400
Next time, we'll see
if you need to take medication.

196
00:13:57,963 --> 00:14:01,480
My boyfriend takes better care
of his health than I do, Doctor.

197
00:14:01,920 --> 00:14:04,287
Why does he still get a tumor?

198
00:14:04,287 --> 00:14:07,040
It can happen due to many factors.

199
00:14:08,096 --> 00:14:11,376
Are tumors caused by stress?

200
00:14:12,542 --> 00:14:15,320
Or is he stressed
because he lives with me?

201
00:14:17,040 --> 00:14:18,600
If the cause were just stress...

202
00:14:19,560 --> 00:14:21,486
everyone in the world
would probably have it.

203
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:24,280
Blaming anyone
doesn't help anything.

204
00:14:24,880 --> 00:14:26,613
Besides, we don't
even know the results yet.

205
00:14:27,080 --> 00:14:31,273
You should get a grip
and calm down first.

206
00:14:56,766 --> 00:14:58,240
Get a grip and calm down.

207
00:14:58,640 --> 00:15:00,106
Get a grip and calm down.

208
00:15:00,106 --> 00:15:02,080
Get a grip and calm down, Ohn.

209
00:15:05,728 --> 00:15:08,828
Thai people die from cancer

210
00:15:08,828 --> 00:15:10,760
at a rate of 227 people a day.

211
00:15:11,936 --> 00:15:15,536
Out of those 227,
Jee can't be one of them.

212
00:15:16,560 --> 00:15:18,400
Calm down, Ohn. Calm down.

213
00:15:18,680 --> 00:15:20,480
Keep it together.

214
00:15:21,240 --> 00:15:22,680
Keep it together.

215
00:15:37,468 --> 00:15:39,255
Itching.
Enlarged tonsils. Chronic cough.

216
00:15:39,255 --> 00:15:41,575
Night sweats. Loss of appetite.
A lump in the throat.

217
00:15:42,873 --> 00:15:44,686
No.

218
00:15:46,366 --> 00:15:48,773
Why can't I stop thinking about it?

219
00:15:49,349 --> 00:15:51,400
I'll just play on my phone instead.

220
00:16:01,148 --> 00:16:03,360
10 Deadly Signs of Cancer.

221
00:16:04,215 --> 00:16:05,215
Jeez.

222
00:16:05,759 --> 00:16:08,326
This damn algorithm
is way too smart.

223
00:16:09,007 --> 00:16:10,560
How does it know
I'm feeling paranoid?

224
00:16:12,507 --> 00:16:14,080
Don't read it. It's too smart.

225
00:16:16,300 --> 00:16:18,520
Pray. Find some spiritual support.

226
00:16:19,520 --> 00:16:21,733
Sacred spirits. Sacred spirits.

227
00:16:21,733 --> 00:16:22,760
Please help me.

228
00:16:22,760 --> 00:16:26,565
Please don't let
my boyfriend have cancer.

229
00:16:26,565 --> 00:16:28,305
Please help your humble servant.

230
00:16:28,305 --> 00:16:31,400
Sacred spirits. Sacred spirits.

231
00:16:35,297 --> 00:16:37,370
Are you Miss Pranee's relatives?

232
00:16:37,370 --> 00:16:38,600
Yes, we are.

233
00:16:39,331 --> 00:16:42,640
We tried our best. I'm so sorry.

234
00:16:44,160 --> 00:16:46,240
Your mother has passed away.

235
00:17:02,631 --> 00:17:03,824
Did you wait long?

236
00:17:04,678 --> 00:17:05,678
Jee...

237
00:17:06,803 --> 00:17:08,240
- Oh!
- Mmm...

238
00:17:10,274 --> 00:17:13,180
It was forever.

239
00:17:13,180 --> 00:17:15,840
It's only been an hour.

240
00:17:17,391 --> 00:17:20,560
But we have to wait
two weeks for the results.

241
00:17:21,360 --> 00:17:24,520
No, that's too long.

242
00:17:24,520 --> 00:17:26,080
It won't be.

243
00:17:27,333 --> 00:17:28,800
There, there.

244
00:18:34,795 --> 00:18:36,928
Is there a reason we're meeting?

245
00:18:42,769 --> 00:18:45,318
I'm more curious about Ohn.

246
00:18:46,160 --> 00:18:49,113
Why do you look
so gloomy and haggard?

247
00:18:49,113 --> 00:18:50,760
Like you've been
cursed or something.

248
00:18:51,624 --> 00:18:53,800
Or did you get some expired Botox?

249
00:18:55,804 --> 00:18:56,850
Silly.

250
00:19:02,127 --> 00:19:03,167
Jee isn't well.

251
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:06,409
Phew!

252
00:19:06,409 --> 00:19:08,317
I thought you were
going to borrow money.

253
00:19:08,317 --> 00:19:09,490
My heart nearly stopped.

254
00:19:09,490 --> 00:19:11,680
Have some empathy for your friend.

255
00:19:12,415 --> 00:19:15,080
Aren't you even going to ask
what's wrong with him?

256
00:19:15,985 --> 00:19:17,000
Mmm.

257
00:19:17,960 --> 00:19:20,080
So, have you arranged the funeral?

258
00:19:33,280 --> 00:19:34,320
It's just that I...

259
00:19:36,880 --> 00:19:39,640
found a tumor in my lymph nodes.

260
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:46,044
Are you serious?

261
00:19:46,978 --> 00:19:50,400
I don't know if it's cancer yet.

262
00:19:51,135 --> 00:19:52,448
Still waiting for the results.

263
00:19:56,173 --> 00:19:57,640
It might turn out to be nothing.

264
00:19:59,280 --> 00:20:00,840
Yeah, but still...

265
00:20:03,280 --> 00:20:04,768
I came to say goodbye

266
00:20:04,768 --> 00:20:06,181
since I know you're all busy.

267
00:20:06,181 --> 00:20:08,720
Just in case, we don't
see each other again.

268
00:20:09,990 --> 00:20:11,361
Jee, come on.

269
00:20:12,560 --> 00:20:13,793
Don't talk like that.

270
00:20:38,080 --> 00:20:39,080
In that case...

271
00:20:39,931 --> 00:20:41,000
How about this?

272
00:20:41,643 --> 00:20:43,025
Before the results come in...

273
00:20:43,954 --> 00:20:45,374
let's do it.

274
00:20:50,446 --> 00:20:51,526
Do what?

275
00:20:52,440 --> 00:20:54,760
A road trip!

276
00:20:55,764 --> 00:20:58,971
Think of it as
a final trip before goodbye.

277
00:20:58,971 --> 00:21:01,280
- Exactly.
- If death really is coming,

278
00:21:01,749 --> 00:21:04,040
we should spend our time together
and make it count.

279
00:21:04,900 --> 00:21:06,173
- Right?
- Exactly.

280
00:21:06,173 --> 00:21:07,200
Mmm-hmm.

281
00:21:48,960 --> 00:21:50,197
Here they are.

282
00:21:50,197 --> 00:21:51,364
Hi, there!

283
00:21:51,364 --> 00:21:52,811
- Hello!
- Hello!

284
00:21:52,811 --> 00:21:54,064
Let's go!

285
00:21:54,064 --> 00:21:55,637
Ranong, Rayong, Lala.

286
00:21:55,637 --> 00:21:57,400
No, it's Ranong, Rayong, Raya.

287
00:21:57,400 --> 00:21:58,520
- No.
- No.

288
00:21:58,520 --> 00:22:00,720
- Ranong, Rayong, Yaya.
- No...

289
00:22:00,720 --> 00:22:02,820
- Ranong, Rayong, Yala.
- No...

290
00:22:02,820 --> 00:22:03,980
That was correct.

291
00:22:03,980 --> 00:22:05,160
Let's just go!

292
00:22:07,095 --> 00:22:08,095
Woo!

293
00:22:09,345 --> 00:22:10,375
There you go.

294
00:22:11,439 --> 00:22:13,080
You almost got me.

295
00:22:13,963 --> 00:22:15,680
- Ready?
- Oh...

296
00:22:17,113 --> 00:22:18,153
Okay, ready?

297
00:22:19,340 --> 00:22:20,360
Go!

298
00:22:21,660 --> 00:22:23,160
Woo...

299
00:22:23,160 --> 00:22:25,320
Ranong, Rayong, Yaya.

300
00:22:43,304 --> 00:22:44,360
No!

301
00:22:45,085 --> 00:22:46,632
My son isn't even dead yet!

302
00:22:46,632 --> 00:22:48,545
How could you even
think of pulling the plug?

303
00:22:48,545 --> 00:22:51,018
Do you even have a heart?

304
00:22:51,018 --> 00:22:52,640
Do you?

305
00:22:54,093 --> 00:22:55,840
But Jee told me...

306
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:57,640
if something like this happened,

307
00:22:58,533 --> 00:22:59,720
he wanted to be let go.

308
00:23:00,760 --> 00:23:01,880
And he also said...

309
00:23:02,757 --> 00:23:04,960
that he wanted me to be
his designated person.

310
00:23:05,320 --> 00:23:06,640
A designated person?

311
00:23:06,960 --> 00:23:09,760
His only designated people
are his father and his mother.

312
00:23:09,760 --> 00:23:11,760
That's right. You're an outsider.

313
00:23:11,760 --> 00:23:13,640
You have no right
to make decisions here.

314
00:23:13,640 --> 00:23:14,747
Understand?

315
00:23:14,747 --> 00:23:16,107
Please stay calm.

316
00:23:16,107 --> 00:23:17,720
Come on, Mom.
Let's go check on our son.

317
00:23:18,504 --> 00:23:19,504
Jee...

318
00:23:24,280 --> 00:23:26,300
The patient's parents
refuse to give consent.

319
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:28,400
There is nothing I can do.

320
00:24:55,120 --> 00:24:56,760
Give your mom and dad some time...

321
00:24:59,480 --> 00:25:01,080
to come to terms with this, Jee.

322
00:25:07,760 --> 00:25:08,760
Soon...

323
00:25:10,680 --> 00:25:11,800
they will probably...

324
00:25:12,884 --> 00:25:14,000
let you go.

325
00:25:17,893 --> 00:25:19,000
If not this year...

326
00:25:20,800 --> 00:25:21,893
then the next year.

327
00:25:23,028 --> 00:25:24,028
Right, Jee?

328
00:25:36,475 --> 00:25:38,440
These wings are absolutely useless.

329
00:25:38,440 --> 00:25:39,486
I'm a goner for sure.

330
00:25:47,680 --> 00:25:49,707
Duckman, are you okay?

331
00:25:49,707 --> 00:25:51,160
Who's this now?

332
00:25:51,160 --> 00:25:53,400
Batman, Birdman, or a Garuda?

333
00:25:53,873 --> 00:25:55,946
I don't know. Maybe an angel?

334
00:25:55,946 --> 00:25:57,600
Take good care of yourself.

335
00:25:59,280 --> 00:26:00,800
Thank you so much.

336
00:26:00,800 --> 00:26:02,240
Don't even know his name.

337
00:26:02,240 --> 00:26:04,693
He's amazing. Dead-cool.

338
00:26:04,693 --> 00:26:09,160
Ooh, Mommy, Daddy, I want him!

339
00:26:10,320 --> 00:26:12,000
"Duckman didn't know who he was."

340
00:26:12,400 --> 00:26:15,347
"He only knew that up in the sky,
amidst the white clouds"

341
00:26:15,347 --> 00:26:18,960
"he was soaring,
living among the birds,"

342
00:26:18,960 --> 00:26:21,046
"joyful and free."

343
00:27:10,240 --> 00:27:11,240
Jee.

344
00:27:13,060 --> 00:27:15,360
It's late. I'm heading back now.

345
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:18,577
I'll come see you again tomorrow.

346
00:27:36,800 --> 00:27:38,003
Goodnight, Jee.

347
00:27:57,466 --> 00:27:58,600
No!

348
00:28:09,413 --> 00:28:10,719
Did you have a nightmare?

349
00:28:13,167 --> 00:28:14,184
Yeah.

350
00:28:15,471 --> 00:28:16,471
A really bad one.

351
00:28:17,065 --> 00:28:19,880
It's okay.

352
00:28:20,963 --> 00:28:23,000
Go back to sleep?

353
00:28:48,350 --> 00:28:49,476
Just close your eyes.

354
00:29:30,610 --> 00:29:33,840
What do you mean cancel?

355
00:29:34,880 --> 00:29:36,920
Cancel as in cancel.

356
00:29:37,400 --> 00:29:40,720
The trip is cancelled
means the whole thing is off.

357
00:29:40,720 --> 00:29:42,520
Jee said he doesn't
want to go anymore.

358
00:29:42,520 --> 00:29:44,120
- What?
- Hey, that's not right.

359
00:29:44,926 --> 00:29:47,626
Wouldn't it be better
to go travel and clear his head?

360
00:29:47,626 --> 00:29:48,793
Mmm.

361
00:29:48,793 --> 00:29:50,473
We've already booked everything.

362
00:29:50,473 --> 00:29:51,919
What am I supposed to do?

363
00:29:51,919 --> 00:29:54,000
Jee said he doesn't want to go.

364
00:29:55,088 --> 00:29:56,522
Hey, behaving like this

365
00:29:57,248 --> 00:29:58,400
is really worrying.

366
00:29:59,025 --> 00:30:00,520
Yesh, I know.

367
00:30:01,160 --> 00:30:04,720
Get him on the phone.
I'll talk to him myself.

368
00:30:05,240 --> 00:30:07,666
Call his number then.
He's not at home.

369
00:30:09,013 --> 00:30:10,200
Where did he go?

370
00:30:10,680 --> 00:30:12,360
He's gone to his parents' house.

371
00:30:12,934 --> 00:30:14,640
Probably to visit his mom and dad.

372
00:30:15,280 --> 00:30:16,320
Ouu...

373
00:30:17,026 --> 00:30:20,560
Is he giving a final sermon
and say his goodbyes?

374
00:30:21,440 --> 00:30:22,440
I don't know.

375
00:30:37,163 --> 00:30:39,320
That was quite a nightmare, son.

376
00:30:40,920 --> 00:30:43,480
Honestly, in your dream...

377
00:30:44,440 --> 00:30:45,887
are we really bad people?

378
00:30:45,887 --> 00:30:47,240
Yeah, exactly.

379
00:30:47,920 --> 00:30:50,800
Do you even have a heart?

380
00:30:50,800 --> 00:30:52,193
Really?

381
00:30:52,193 --> 00:30:53,960
Did you really think I'd say that?

382
00:30:54,339 --> 00:30:57,059
- I didn't think so, but...
- But what?

383
00:30:57,059 --> 00:31:00,280
Probably I was just anxious.

384
00:31:00,600 --> 00:31:01,840
Nonsense.

385
00:31:03,061 --> 00:31:04,274
When will you get the results?

386
00:31:04,920 --> 00:31:05,920
Well...

387
00:31:06,858 --> 00:31:07,880
Next week.

388
00:31:08,720 --> 00:31:12,220
You'll be fine.
I'll be waiting for the good news.

389
00:31:12,220 --> 00:31:14,520
It's 50/50, Mom.

390
00:31:15,033 --> 00:31:16,760
Anything could happen.

391
00:31:18,920 --> 00:31:22,360
The reason I'm telling you this

392
00:31:22,929 --> 00:31:26,029
is because I want you to know
that if anything happens to me...

393
00:31:28,678 --> 00:31:29,871
I want Ohn...

394
00:31:30,959 --> 00:31:32,800
to be the one making the decisions.

395
00:31:34,970 --> 00:31:36,520
This is to let you know,

396
00:31:37,423 --> 00:31:38,680
not a request.

397
00:31:49,080 --> 00:31:50,080
Okay.

398
00:31:50,920 --> 00:31:52,560
In that case, we acknowledge it.

399
00:31:54,320 --> 00:31:55,320
We agree to that.

400
00:31:56,400 --> 00:31:58,320
Since you've made your decision,

401
00:31:58,785 --> 00:32:01,600
don't forget to put it in writing.

402
00:32:08,040 --> 00:32:09,200
Why was that so easy?

403
00:32:09,640 --> 00:32:12,247
- Why would it have to be hard?
- Yeah.

404
00:32:12,247 --> 00:32:14,240
You're a grown man.

405
00:32:14,920 --> 00:32:17,360
You should be able to
make your own life decisions.

406
00:32:19,080 --> 00:32:22,400
But if it's my turn first...

407
00:32:24,640 --> 00:32:26,600
and you kids
have to make the decision

408
00:32:28,160 --> 00:32:29,240
you have to promise me

409
00:32:30,051 --> 00:32:32,440
that you will convince
Jang and Jirote

410
00:32:33,675 --> 00:32:35,280
to let me go peacefully.

411
00:32:35,880 --> 00:32:37,320
Don't let me suffer.

412
00:32:37,760 --> 00:32:39,513
All that life support stuff,

413
00:32:40,160 --> 00:32:42,600
you don't want it. Neither do I.

414
00:32:43,078 --> 00:32:44,078
Mmm.

415
00:32:44,715 --> 00:32:46,988
- I don't want it either.
- Yeah.

416
00:32:46,988 --> 00:32:48,785
Look at you two,

417
00:32:48,785 --> 00:32:51,675
old folks giving out last wishes.

418
00:32:51,675 --> 00:32:54,440
- You!
- Like you're not old yourself.

419
00:32:54,440 --> 00:32:56,260
- Yeah.
- Those gray hairs on your head.

420
00:32:56,260 --> 00:32:57,760
Almost catching up to us.

421
00:32:57,760 --> 00:32:59,600
Right here.

422
00:32:59,600 --> 00:33:01,320
Well, I'm not arguing with that.

423
00:33:02,740 --> 00:33:06,866
Do you remember when
your Grandma was about to pass?

424
00:33:15,664 --> 00:33:17,440
Mom.

425
00:33:20,153 --> 00:33:21,660
She is our mother.

426
00:33:22,760 --> 00:33:24,200
This is our mother!

427
00:33:25,560 --> 00:33:27,680
Are you really
going to do this to her?

428
00:33:28,453 --> 00:33:30,160
You don't want to
take care of her, do you?

429
00:33:30,160 --> 00:33:31,426
You ungrateful son!

430
00:33:34,120 --> 00:33:35,513
How much could it be?

431
00:33:37,322 --> 00:33:39,968
How much is the treatment for Mom?

432
00:33:40,600 --> 00:33:41,906
I'll pay for it myself.

433
00:33:43,720 --> 00:33:44,960
It's not like that!

434
00:33:45,400 --> 00:33:46,600
Mom loved you the most.

435
00:33:47,784 --> 00:33:49,320
Why do you see her as a burden?

436
00:33:49,894 --> 00:33:51,214
You're not my brother anymore!

437
00:33:51,880 --> 00:33:53,327
Calm down.

438
00:33:53,327 --> 00:33:55,573
He's just doing what she'd ordered.

439
00:33:55,573 --> 00:33:58,800
You're just a daughter-in-law.
Don't interfere in family business.

440
00:33:58,800 --> 00:34:00,240
You shut your mouth, Jook!

441
00:34:01,400 --> 00:34:02,400
Shut up!

442
00:34:05,780 --> 00:34:06,820
Shut up, you say?

443
00:34:09,238 --> 00:34:10,960
You shut up, you ungrateful brat!

444
00:34:10,960 --> 00:34:12,000
What is wrong with you?

445
00:34:12,000 --> 00:34:13,667
What are you gonna do?

446
00:34:13,667 --> 00:34:16,100
- Listen to me, damn it!
- Let go of me!

447
00:34:17,240 --> 00:34:19,327
- Don't you dare!
- Listen for once!

448
00:34:19,327 --> 00:34:20,446
Come at me!

449
00:34:23,052 --> 00:34:24,120
Ungrateful son!

450
00:34:26,989 --> 00:34:30,040
The two children who never
even bothered to look after her

451
00:34:30,528 --> 00:34:32,210
suddenly became devoted children

452
00:34:32,210 --> 00:34:33,670
and wouldn't let them
pull the plug

453
00:34:34,196 --> 00:34:37,742
inspite of her wish
not to use a ventilator.

454
00:34:39,040 --> 00:34:41,320
Before we could follow her wish,

455
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:44,800
- we almost cut ties as siblings.
- Mmm.

456
00:34:45,209 --> 00:34:47,480
Back then, your dad
cried every single day.

457
00:34:47,969 --> 00:34:50,480
I never knew about this.

458
00:34:51,000 --> 00:34:53,553
Why should you?
You were still a child.

459
00:34:53,553 --> 00:34:55,647
Who would tell
these kinds of things to children?

460
00:34:55,647 --> 00:34:56,840
Mmm.

461
00:34:56,840 --> 00:35:00,060
After that, there was all the chaos
about dividing the inheritance.

462
00:35:00,060 --> 00:35:01,100
Mmm.

463
00:35:01,100 --> 00:35:02,886
We fought like crazy

464
00:35:03,345 --> 00:35:05,479
even though the money
wasn't even that much.

465
00:35:06,116 --> 00:35:10,149
It's because your parents didn't
get things sorted out properly.

466
00:35:10,149 --> 00:35:11,980
That's why
you faced those problems.

467
00:35:13,120 --> 00:35:15,160
In the old days,
people were superstitious.

468
00:35:16,520 --> 00:35:18,280
They thought it wasn't a big deal.

469
00:35:18,280 --> 00:35:19,927
Left it to the siblings to manage.

470
00:35:19,927 --> 00:35:21,153
Mmm.

471
00:35:21,153 --> 00:35:23,973
Little did they know, the siblings
themselves are the big problem.

472
00:35:23,973 --> 00:35:25,080
- Mmm.
- Mmm.

473
00:35:25,920 --> 00:35:29,633
Speaking of which,
we haven't made our wills yet.

474
00:35:29,633 --> 00:35:31,720
- Yeah.
- We really should.

475
00:35:32,400 --> 00:35:35,120
I keep saying I'll do it,
but then I always forget.

476
00:35:35,586 --> 00:35:37,520
We should hurry up and do it.

477
00:35:37,520 --> 00:35:40,000
So we don't leave
problems behind for the kids.

478
00:35:40,000 --> 00:35:42,560
I'm planning to make a will too.

479
00:35:44,480 --> 00:35:46,480
Do we need to hire a lawyer?
Is it expensive?

480
00:35:47,720 --> 00:35:52,233
Not at all. I'm going to
make a Public Document will.

481
00:35:52,233 --> 00:35:55,520
- A Public Document Will?
- Mmm.

482
00:35:55,520 --> 00:35:57,706
It's where you
go to the district office

483
00:35:57,706 --> 00:35:59,559
and let the officials
handle it for you.

484
00:35:59,559 --> 00:36:01,440
Oh, can't we write it ourselves?

485
00:36:01,440 --> 00:36:02,556
You can.

486
00:36:02,556 --> 00:36:04,610
You write the whole thing yourself.

487
00:36:04,610 --> 00:36:07,476
You can write it at home,
and you don't even need witnesses.

488
00:36:07,476 --> 00:36:11,480
But you must not forget
the important details.

489
00:36:12,080 --> 00:36:14,960
Such as the date the will was made.

490
00:36:14,960 --> 00:36:18,040
And if you make
any corrections anywhere...

491
00:36:18,432 --> 00:36:20,680
if you forget to sign
to authorize them...

492
00:36:21,648 --> 00:36:23,648
that will becomes invalid.

493
00:36:24,440 --> 00:36:25,840
That's important.

494
00:36:26,720 --> 00:36:28,960
Yes, so I'm going to
have the officials do it.

495
00:36:28,960 --> 00:36:31,166
Because I can be
quite sure of its accuracy.

496
00:36:31,720 --> 00:36:34,600
Most importantly,
the fee is less than 100 Baht.

497
00:36:34,920 --> 00:36:36,033
- Really?
- Oh!

498
00:36:37,080 --> 00:36:39,040
What documents do we need?

499
00:36:39,040 --> 00:36:43,100
Well, there's the originals of
your ID card, house registration,

500
00:36:43,100 --> 00:36:45,367
documents proving
ownership of assets,

501
00:36:45,367 --> 00:36:46,920
such as land title deeds.

502
00:36:47,440 --> 00:36:49,600
And you also need two witnesses.

503
00:36:50,160 --> 00:36:53,680
Oh, and since you are over 60,
you'll need a medical certificate

504
00:36:53,680 --> 00:36:59,487
to certify that you are
of sound mind and fully competent.

505
00:36:59,487 --> 00:37:00,569
That's all.

506
00:37:00,569 --> 00:37:01,882
Mom really needs to do it soon.

507
00:37:02,315 --> 00:37:04,200
You're so forgetful,
you might get Alzheimer's.

508
00:37:04,200 --> 00:37:06,080
Look at that,
turning it on me like that.

509
00:37:09,280 --> 00:37:10,480
You're older than me.

510
00:37:16,815 --> 00:37:18,595
Deep-fried chicken.

511
00:37:19,375 --> 00:37:21,415
Smells amazing.

512
00:37:21,415 --> 00:37:23,968
The dipping sauce looks so good.

513
00:37:23,968 --> 00:37:26,248
Why did you come back so soon?

514
00:37:28,272 --> 00:37:29,367
Hey.

515
00:37:29,367 --> 00:37:32,092
Jira, you're back way too early.

516
00:37:32,092 --> 00:37:35,800
The surprise is ruined.

517
00:37:36,506 --> 00:37:37,626
What surprise?

518
00:37:38,294 --> 00:37:41,041
Well, it's like this.

519
00:37:41,041 --> 00:37:44,921
We planned to
turn off all the lights

520
00:37:44,921 --> 00:37:48,880
and wait for you to come back
before surprising you.

521
00:37:49,466 --> 00:37:52,379
Popping party poppers,
singing songs, that kind of thing.

522
00:37:52,379 --> 00:37:53,499
Mmm.

523
00:37:53,499 --> 00:37:56,800
We planned it so well,
but you just came back too early.

524
00:37:59,600 --> 00:38:01,400
How about this,
since they're already here,

525
00:38:01,400 --> 00:38:04,109
- Can you step outside for a bit?
- Hmm?

526
00:38:04,109 --> 00:38:05,400
Then come back in again.

527
00:38:05,400 --> 00:38:08,360
And pretend to be surprised
to make them happy.

528
00:38:08,360 --> 00:38:10,467
Come on, for their effort.

529
00:38:10,467 --> 00:38:11,880
Please? Go on out for a second.

530
00:38:11,880 --> 00:38:13,800
Wait, it's not even my birthday.

531
00:38:13,800 --> 00:38:16,960
Just play along.

532
00:38:16,960 --> 00:38:19,427
It doesn't have to be
a birthday to have a surprise.

533
00:38:19,427 --> 00:38:23,013
- Yeah.
- It's a way to show that we care.

534
00:38:23,013 --> 00:38:26,000
We all want you to feel better.

535
00:38:30,080 --> 00:38:33,120
This is surprise enough.

536
00:38:34,200 --> 00:38:35,286
Thanks, guys.

537
00:38:35,840 --> 00:38:38,687
And I'm sorry
for cancelling the trip.

538
00:38:38,687 --> 00:38:41,380
I really wasn't
in the mood to go anywhere.

539
00:38:41,380 --> 00:38:43,600
Don't apologize. It's fine.

540
00:38:44,063 --> 00:38:46,846
- Are you hungry?
- Let's eat.

541
00:38:47,600 --> 00:38:48,600
Yum.

542
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:52,200
Hello? Oh, you've arrived?

543
00:38:52,920 --> 00:38:54,760
Wait in the lobby, please.
I'll be right down.

544
00:38:54,760 --> 00:38:56,453
I'll go get the drinks first.

545
00:38:56,453 --> 00:38:57,620
Be right back.

546
00:38:57,620 --> 00:38:59,891
- I'll help.
- Alright, let's go.

547
00:39:10,960 --> 00:39:11,960
Hey...

548
00:39:12,320 --> 00:39:13,320
What?

549
00:39:14,480 --> 00:39:15,880
If anything happens to me...

550
00:39:18,220 --> 00:39:19,520
You have to look after Ohn.

551
00:39:25,255 --> 00:39:26,800
Take him out.

552
00:39:27,170 --> 00:39:28,603
Make sure he eats.

553
00:39:28,603 --> 00:39:30,583
Make him do some work so he...

554
00:39:31,653 --> 00:39:34,844
doesn't get sad,
lonely, or go crazy.

555
00:39:36,711 --> 00:39:38,197
Sure thing, I got you...

556
00:39:41,120 --> 00:39:44,146
Seriously though,
you two are exactly alike.

557
00:39:44,968 --> 00:39:47,160
Ohn told me the exact same thing.

558
00:39:47,160 --> 00:39:48,925
That if anything happens to him...

559
00:39:49,597 --> 00:39:52,320
he asked us to look after you.

560
00:39:52,706 --> 00:39:53,860
Mmm.

561
00:39:54,320 --> 00:39:56,480
You two care for
each other so much.

562
00:39:57,485 --> 00:39:59,745
Honestly, just don't let
anything happen to you.

563
00:39:59,745 --> 00:40:02,320
Because I would probably
get really annoyed with Ohn.

564
00:40:03,040 --> 00:40:05,520
He'd probably be such a mess.

565
00:40:06,573 --> 00:40:07,573
Alright then.

566
00:40:08,600 --> 00:40:09,720
I'll try.

567
00:40:11,400 --> 00:40:12,400
Okay.

568
00:40:14,360 --> 00:40:17,167
Jee... Jee, Jee, Jee, Jee!

569
00:40:17,167 --> 00:40:19,633
- What?
- Who died?

570
00:40:22,133 --> 00:40:25,160
Nobody died. But, good news!

571
00:40:25,680 --> 00:40:27,200
The publisher called and said

572
00:40:27,724 --> 00:40:29,840
the spin-off project
has been greenlit.

573
00:40:29,840 --> 00:40:33,033
I'll get to write
a special Duckman series!

574
00:40:33,033 --> 00:40:37,760
- Yay! Congrats, Ohn!
- Hey, that's cool!

575
00:40:37,760 --> 00:40:40,005
- Awesome!
- Woo... yes!

576
00:40:41,320 --> 00:40:43,940
Time for the party poppers!

577
00:40:43,940 --> 00:40:46,185
Wait, hold on a second.

578
00:40:46,185 --> 00:40:48,745
Why? We're celebrating
the good news.

579
00:40:48,745 --> 00:40:50,652
- Mmm.
- Don't let them go to waste.

580
00:40:50,652 --> 00:40:54,578
But if you pop that now,
they will fall in the food.

581
00:40:54,578 --> 00:40:55,640
We can't eat them.

582
00:40:55,640 --> 00:40:58,880
- Oh, right.
- Let's do it later then.

583
00:40:58,880 --> 00:41:00,907
Come on, let's eat.

584
00:41:00,907 --> 00:41:02,967
Yay! Yay!

585
00:41:02,967 --> 00:41:04,073
I'm so happy!

586
00:41:05,468 --> 00:41:06,868
Eat your vegetables.

587
00:41:08,665 --> 00:41:11,432
- Good, right?
- Is the sauce spicy?

588
00:41:11,432 --> 00:41:12,800
The sauce is good.

589
00:41:14,178 --> 00:41:15,898
Is it lit?
"Filming under security control."

590
00:41:15,898 --> 00:41:17,191
- It's lit!
- Yay...

591
00:41:17,191 --> 00:41:18,498
Whoa!

592
00:41:18,498 --> 00:41:21,298
- Another one.
- Ooh, it's great.

593
00:41:21,298 --> 00:41:23,960
Look, I'm drawing eyes.

594
00:41:23,960 --> 00:41:25,560
Will people think
we're asking for help?

595
00:41:26,720 --> 00:41:28,200
Help me!

596
00:41:29,995 --> 00:41:31,021
Like this?

597
00:41:31,487 --> 00:41:33,114
- Woo!
- Yay!

598
00:41:33,114 --> 00:41:36,727
- Yay!
- Woo! Woo!

599
00:41:36,727 --> 00:41:38,000
Yours looks like an O.

600
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:39,940
Here, it's an O.

601
00:41:39,940 --> 00:41:42,567
Oh, yeah! That's an O now.

602
00:41:42,567 --> 00:41:45,334
- It's all gone.
- Gone now.

603
00:41:45,334 --> 00:41:47,667
All done.

604
00:41:48,356 --> 00:41:51,000
Life is just this, isn't it?

605
00:41:51,890 --> 00:41:53,640
What is "this"?

606
00:41:55,180 --> 00:41:58,760
To shines brightly for a moment,
then simply fades away.

607
00:42:02,920 --> 00:42:05,480
When the time comes
for us to leave this world,

608
00:42:06,160 --> 00:42:10,000
who's going to think about
or judge their success

609
00:42:10,000 --> 00:42:11,360
by title or position?

610
00:42:11,360 --> 00:42:14,760
Or the money
you have in your account?

611
00:42:15,400 --> 00:42:16,913
Who cares? Who would think that?

612
00:42:22,640 --> 00:42:24,960
I would care.

613
00:42:29,200 --> 00:42:30,360
No.

614
00:42:31,640 --> 00:42:32,840
In the end, it's just...

615
00:42:33,800 --> 00:42:37,080
In this life, who did we ever love?

616
00:42:38,160 --> 00:42:41,702
And were we ever
truly loved by someone?

617
00:42:42,671 --> 00:42:43,797
Isn't that all there is?

618
00:42:47,000 --> 00:42:48,920
Whoa...

619
00:42:51,280 --> 00:42:53,680
I didn't know you were like this.

620
00:42:55,080 --> 00:42:57,127
My darling has
always been like this.

621
00:42:57,127 --> 00:42:58,280
Really?

622
00:42:58,280 --> 00:43:00,720
He's deep and philosophical.

623
00:43:02,500 --> 00:43:03,506
Mmm...

624
00:43:03,998 --> 00:43:07,251
Then how come did he
choose you as a boyfriend?

625
00:43:07,251 --> 00:43:08,778
- Whoa!
- Hey!

626
00:43:11,803 --> 00:43:13,369
There, there.

627
00:43:13,369 --> 00:43:16,903
Darling, I don't want to
associate with these two anymore.

628
00:43:16,903 --> 00:43:18,616
- Oh!
- They're not nice.

629
00:43:18,616 --> 00:43:20,256
Someone's pouting.

630
00:43:20,256 --> 00:43:22,560
I was just teasing you.

631
00:43:23,000 --> 00:43:25,073
There's still some sparklers left.

632
00:43:25,073 --> 00:43:27,097
Keep lighting them. Don't fight.

633
00:43:27,674 --> 00:43:30,272
- Keep lighting.
- Come on.

634
00:43:30,272 --> 00:43:32,840
- There it is!
- Woo...

635
00:43:33,679 --> 00:43:36,361
Woo-hoo! Woo!

636
00:43:47,381 --> 00:43:48,974
Please check
if everything is correct.

637
00:43:48,974 --> 00:43:51,481
Then you and
the two witnesses can sign.

638
00:43:51,481 --> 00:43:52,560
Yes, thank you.

639
00:44:13,383 --> 00:44:14,443
Okay.

640
00:44:14,443 --> 00:44:15,555
Thank you.

641
00:44:19,434 --> 00:44:22,634
All set. I'll have
the District Director noterize it.

642
00:44:22,634 --> 00:44:24,594
- Thank you very much.
- Please wait a moment.

643
00:44:24,594 --> 00:44:25,640
Yes.

644
00:44:36,708 --> 00:44:37,857
Thank you so much

645
00:44:37,857 --> 00:44:39,881
for taking time off work
to be my witnesses.

646
00:44:40,360 --> 00:44:43,713
- You're relieved now, right?
- Mmm.

647
00:44:43,713 --> 00:44:45,527
If you really want to thank us,

648
00:44:45,527 --> 00:44:47,831
you should give us
two or three million.

649
00:44:47,856 --> 00:44:49,800
Take it easy.

650
00:44:50,549 --> 00:44:53,861
Hey, a beneficiary in a will

651
00:44:53,861 --> 00:44:55,847
is prohibited from
being a witness, you know.

652
00:44:55,847 --> 00:44:59,760
Why don't you
get married to Ohn then?

653
00:45:00,529 --> 00:45:02,004
Mmm.

654
00:45:02,004 --> 00:45:05,242
Say, how much inheritance
does a spouse get...

655
00:45:06,070 --> 00:45:07,324
if they don't have children?

656
00:45:07,324 --> 00:45:10,857
If parents are still alive,
it's divided by three.

657
00:45:10,857 --> 00:45:12,800
The spouse gets one-third.

658
00:45:13,423 --> 00:45:16,874
But if only one parent left,
they each get one half.

659
00:45:17,230 --> 00:45:20,943
If the parents are gone,
the spouse gets half.

660
00:45:20,943 --> 00:45:23,503
The rest is divided
among the siblings.

661
00:45:23,503 --> 00:45:25,585
That's good then.

662
00:45:25,585 --> 00:45:27,292
Why don't you
register the marriage?

663
00:45:28,325 --> 00:45:30,998
Well, it's because of my parents.

664
00:45:30,998 --> 00:45:34,065
My mom can accept it now.

665
00:45:34,065 --> 00:45:37,009
But there's still
some lingering hesitation.

666
00:45:37,611 --> 00:45:38,944
But as for my dad,

667
00:45:38,944 --> 00:45:43,480
I don't know if he
would be heartbroken or not.

668
00:45:44,680 --> 00:45:46,253
Poor thing...

669
00:45:46,253 --> 00:45:49,627
We don't even know
when we're going to die,

670
00:45:49,627 --> 00:45:51,400
yet we still have to care

671
00:45:51,400 --> 00:45:53,640
and worry about
other people's feelings.

672
00:45:54,105 --> 00:45:56,360
Isn't our life our own?

673
00:45:58,880 --> 00:46:00,560
Well, it's his life.

674
00:46:01,136 --> 00:46:04,970
He has already
thought this through.

675
00:46:05,304 --> 00:46:07,255
You're here to be a witness,
just be a witness.

676
00:46:07,255 --> 00:46:08,910
No need to judge anyone.

677
00:46:09,691 --> 00:46:12,200
Everyone has
different circumstances, right?

678
00:46:14,240 --> 00:46:15,400
Well said.

679
00:46:16,452 --> 00:46:19,080
- Mmm.
- Speaking of which...

680
00:46:19,840 --> 00:46:22,381
People like us
have to plan our finances

681
00:46:22,381 --> 00:46:24,907
- and take good care of ourselves.
- Mmm.

682
00:46:24,907 --> 00:46:27,748
Because we probably
won't have children

683
00:46:27,748 --> 00:46:30,173
to look after us when we're sick.

684
00:46:30,173 --> 00:46:33,447
Even for straight couples,

685
00:46:33,447 --> 00:46:36,307
nowadays, you can't expect
to rely on your children

686
00:46:36,307 --> 00:46:40,880
because everyone
is struggling to survive

687
00:46:41,920 --> 00:46:46,387
That's why I've started
taking better care of my health.

688
00:46:46,387 --> 00:46:48,225
I don't want to get sick.

689
00:46:48,225 --> 00:46:50,358
I don't want Job to have to worry

690
00:46:50,358 --> 00:46:51,640
or have to look after me.

691
00:46:52,480 --> 00:46:53,620
Mr. A, please.

692
00:46:54,240 --> 00:46:57,000
You told me you joined the gym
because there're hot guys there.

693
00:46:57,915 --> 00:46:59,835
Yes, the eye candies are great.

694
00:46:59,835 --> 00:47:02,520
Seeing something
beautiful and captivating

695
00:47:02,520 --> 00:47:05,040
is like doing cardio
in its own way.

696
00:47:07,176 --> 00:47:10,209
I can go there because I'm single.

697
00:47:10,209 --> 00:47:12,336
But if you want to do cardio,

698
00:47:12,336 --> 00:47:14,515
wouldn't it be easier
to just go to Job?

699
00:47:15,760 --> 00:47:16,760
Mmm.

700
00:47:17,662 --> 00:47:18,702
You!

701
00:47:23,985 --> 00:47:25,465
Congrats, man.

702
00:47:25,926 --> 00:47:27,707
The Duckman project finally passed.

703
00:47:27,707 --> 00:47:29,731
You've been pushing
for this for so long.

704
00:47:30,067 --> 00:47:31,067
Mmm.

705
00:47:31,840 --> 00:47:33,120
Thanks a lot.

706
00:47:35,160 --> 00:47:38,320
Ohn, we also have some
wonderful news to share.

707
00:47:39,840 --> 00:47:40,840
What?

708
00:47:42,175 --> 00:47:45,080
Don't tell me that...

709
00:47:46,089 --> 00:47:48,360
that you are...

710
00:47:49,560 --> 00:47:50,560
pregnant?

711
00:47:51,390 --> 00:47:53,337
- Ohn!
- You idiot.

712
00:47:53,337 --> 00:47:55,920
I'm just bloated, not pregnant.

713
00:47:57,200 --> 00:48:00,113
Nidnoi and I
are going to register our marriage.

714
00:48:00,113 --> 00:48:01,507
- Whoa!
- Because...

715
00:48:01,507 --> 00:48:03,533
Nidnoi got a visa to work abroad.

716
00:48:03,533 --> 00:48:07,093
I'll be able to apply for
a dependent visa as her spouse.

717
00:48:07,093 --> 00:48:08,200
Mmm.

718
00:48:09,272 --> 00:48:12,612
Could you and Jee come be witnesses
at the district office for us?

719
00:48:13,442 --> 00:48:16,329
Sure. I'm happy for both of you.

720
00:48:16,329 --> 00:48:18,280
Just let me know which day.

721
00:48:19,103 --> 00:48:22,280
Well, since I have to go
to the district office,

722
00:48:23,462 --> 00:48:25,800
should I go ahead
and make a will too?

723
00:48:27,176 --> 00:48:29,800
Ohn, are you about to die?

724
00:48:30,200 --> 00:48:31,286
Ouch.

725
00:48:33,474 --> 00:48:34,580
Don't be surprised.

726
00:48:34,935 --> 00:48:37,428
His face has always looked
like someone on the verge of death.

727
00:48:37,428 --> 00:48:39,609
When looking at his face,

728
00:48:39,609 --> 00:48:41,661
just think of it
as meditating on a corpse.

729
00:48:41,661 --> 00:48:43,472
Hey, Chon!

730
00:48:44,493 --> 00:48:45,546
Enlightenment.

731
00:48:46,240 --> 00:48:47,706
The body is impermanent.

732
00:48:49,013 --> 00:48:51,138
You two...

733
00:48:52,146 --> 00:48:55,120
Please respect my Botox.
Look how tight it is.

734
00:48:55,706 --> 00:48:57,046
Can you at least act hesitant?

735
00:48:59,260 --> 00:49:01,385
So, about Jee...

736
00:49:02,272 --> 00:49:03,320
When will you find out?

737
00:49:06,241 --> 00:49:08,560
Terrible timing.

738
00:49:09,550 --> 00:49:11,080
He's upset now.

739
00:49:12,640 --> 00:49:14,460
I asked because I'm worried.

740
00:49:14,460 --> 00:49:16,339
I care.

741
00:49:17,280 --> 00:49:19,640
Why are you acting
all hesitant and fidgety?

742
00:49:20,246 --> 00:49:22,400
Whatever happens, happens.

743
00:49:23,040 --> 00:49:25,920
So, when will you know the result?

744
00:49:27,726 --> 00:49:28,813
Tomorrow.

745
00:49:32,426 --> 00:49:33,526
Could it be...

746
00:49:34,386 --> 00:49:37,126
what the fortune teller said about
Jee and me having to break up?

747
00:49:38,206 --> 00:49:39,206
Does it mean...

748
00:49:40,160 --> 00:49:41,859
we'll be parted by death?

749
00:49:42,844 --> 00:49:46,080
Chon, I'm scared.

750
00:49:47,233 --> 00:49:49,453
Ohn, what are you afraid of?

751
00:49:50,320 --> 00:49:52,120
Everyone has to be parted by death.

752
00:49:54,111 --> 00:49:56,480
Ohn, Jee will be fine.

753
00:49:57,120 --> 00:50:01,726
Look at her, she's made vows
at shrines all over the place.

754
00:50:02,342 --> 00:50:04,760
Fulfilling all those vows
will take at least a year.

755
00:50:05,310 --> 00:50:07,196
So when exactly
are we going to fly to Canada?

756
00:50:07,977 --> 00:50:10,137
It's okay. We'll go to Canada.

757
00:50:10,720 --> 00:50:13,013
Whatever vows are left,
he can help fulfill them.

758
00:50:13,013 --> 00:50:14,560
- True.
- Right?

759
00:50:14,560 --> 00:50:18,260
So, when the two of us
are no longer here

760
00:50:18,260 --> 00:50:21,203
you have to
take good care of yourself.

761
00:50:21,538 --> 00:50:24,240
Take care of your health, exercise,

762
00:50:24,240 --> 00:50:26,380
get a check-up every year,

763
00:50:26,380 --> 00:50:28,880
and most importantly, eat clean.

764
00:50:31,400 --> 00:50:33,520
Am I really going
to be left all alone?

765
00:50:34,476 --> 00:50:37,121
If you're all alone, you have to
take even better care of yourself.

766
00:50:37,121 --> 00:50:38,707
Double the effort, you know?

767
00:50:39,273 --> 00:50:41,880
You have to be
a good-looking widower.

768
00:50:42,160 --> 00:50:43,840
You can't let yourself fall apart.

769
00:50:44,560 --> 00:50:45,680
Do you understand?

770
00:50:46,408 --> 00:50:50,000
Jee isn't even dead yet,
but you already look this worn out.

771
00:50:50,400 --> 00:50:52,320
If he dies, what then?
What state will you be in?

772
00:50:52,320 --> 00:50:53,400
Ugh...

773
00:50:54,022 --> 00:50:57,080
Why are you two
insulting me like this?

774
00:50:58,366 --> 00:51:00,840
We're just teasing.

775
00:51:01,880 --> 00:51:04,320
It's just our way
of showing that we care.

776
00:51:07,440 --> 00:51:08,900
Stay strong, okay?

777
00:51:55,080 --> 00:51:57,080
Mr. Jira, please wait here
for a moment.

778
00:51:57,080 --> 00:52:00,280
Lots of patients today,
so it might take a while.

779
00:52:01,281 --> 00:52:02,281
Thank you.

780
00:52:09,723 --> 00:52:11,320
Jee.

781
00:52:11,857 --> 00:52:13,524
Did you get any sleep last night?

782
00:52:13,524 --> 00:52:15,457
Mmm...

783
00:52:15,457 --> 00:52:17,520
A little bit. How about you?

784
00:52:18,681 --> 00:52:21,039
I saw you working all night.
Aren't you tired?

785
00:52:21,632 --> 00:52:24,492
Honestly, you didn't have to
come today. I'm fine.

786
00:52:24,492 --> 00:52:25,625
Don't be silly.

787
00:52:26,123 --> 00:52:28,640
How could I not come?

788
00:52:38,123 --> 00:52:39,840
Hey, are you mocking me?

789
00:52:41,030 --> 00:52:42,400
It's contagious.

790
00:52:52,920 --> 00:52:54,000
"Let's stay together,"

791
00:52:54,386 --> 00:52:55,673
"until the day we die."

792
00:52:56,840 --> 00:52:59,840
"We all want you to feel better."

793
00:53:02,840 --> 00:53:04,360
"If anything happens to me,"

794
00:53:05,711 --> 00:53:07,080
"you have to look after Ohn."

795
00:53:08,309 --> 00:53:09,680
"Sure thing, I got you."

796
00:53:11,716 --> 00:53:14,960
"You'll be fine.
I'll be waiting for the good news."

797
00:53:41,501 --> 00:53:43,720
Mr. Jira, the doctor
is ready for you.

798
00:53:44,280 --> 00:53:45,480
Mr. Jira?

799
00:53:46,360 --> 00:53:47,360
Mr. Jira.

800
00:54:02,069 --> 00:54:04,960
I care about you, Liu,
and I want to protect you.

801
00:54:04,960 --> 00:54:06,760
Then what was all that before?

802
00:54:06,760 --> 00:54:09,413
Do you actually like me,
or are you just waiting for a man?

803
00:54:09,413 --> 00:54:10,487
Ohn,

804
00:54:10,487 --> 00:54:12,280
Jee seems like such a calm person.

805
00:54:12,640 --> 00:54:15,720
He's not calm about everything.

806
00:54:15,720 --> 00:54:17,960
But he's always kind.

807
00:54:18,269 --> 00:54:20,120
- Mmm...
- Oh, wait...

808
00:54:20,453 --> 00:54:22,040
The results of your biopsy are in.

809
00:54:22,400 --> 00:54:26,693
Even if we're old, we've still
got some strength for our age.

810
00:54:26,693 --> 00:54:28,080
Whoa!

811
00:54:28,680 --> 00:54:29,813
It's morning now.

812
00:54:29,813 --> 00:54:31,837
I'd better hurry up and move on.

813
00:54:32,548 --> 00:54:37,480
♪ Can you feel
that love still remains? ♪

814
00:54:37,480 --> 00:54:43,720
♪ Can you feel
the stories we made? ♪

815
00:54:43,720 --> 00:54:48,867
♪ No matter what stood in our way ♪

816
00:54:48,867 --> 00:54:50,891
♪ Come rain or shine ♪

817
00:54:52,712 --> 00:54:57,720
♪ Can you feel
the love from the start? ♪

818
00:54:57,720 --> 00:55:03,960
♪ Can you feel
the beat of my heart? ♪

819
00:55:03,960 --> 00:55:09,560
♪ Calling out so we never part ♪

820
00:55:09,560 --> 00:55:14,280
♪ Every day together
Forever you and I ♪

821
00:55:14,280 --> 00:55:18,760
♪ La la la la la la la ♪

822
00:55:19,200 --> 00:55:23,840
♪ La la la la la la la ♪

823
